70@@printf "This program loads a cgroup skb BPF program to enforce
" "cgroup output (egress) bandwidth limits.

" "USAGE: hbm [-o] [-d]  [-l] [-n <id>] [--no_cn] [-r <rate>]
" "           [-s] [-t <secs>] [-w] [-h] [prog]
" "  Where:
" "    -o         indicates egress direction (default)
" "    -d         print BPF trace debug buffer
" "    -l         also limit flows using loopback
" "    -n <#>     to create cgroup "/hbm#" and attach prog
" "               Default is /hbm1
" "    --no_cn    disable CN notifcations
" "    -r <rate>  Rate in Mbps
" "    -s         Update HBM stats
" "    -t <time>  Exit after specified seconds (default is 0)
" "    -w	       Work conserving flag. cgroup can increase
" "               bandwidth beyond the rate limit specified
" "               while there is available bandwidth. Current
" "               implementation assumes there is only eth0
" "               but can be extended to support multiple NICs
" "    -h         print this info
" "    prog       BPF program file name. Name defaults to
" "                 hbm_out_kern.o
"
